<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36121n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36121n">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36121n"> 121(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> St Andrew Undershaft.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>St Andrew Undershaft</mark>, so named because a Maypole used to be set up before the former church on May-day, is late Perpendicular (c. 1530) and contains a monument to John Stow the chronicler (d. 1605). <small> &ldquo;LONDON&rdquo; <a name="EBLO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBLO"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 941d</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
